", "w": "14616"}, {"t": "Squatty Roo", "c": "Johnny Hodges", "w": "5814"}, {"t": "New York City Blues", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "29389"}, {"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "18966", "date": "1948-11-13", "label": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["alto_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Brown Betty", "c": "Billy Strayhorn", "w": "16944"}]}, {"id": "20316", "date": "1964-03-29", "label": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["alto_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41777", "date": "1967-03-26", "label": "Jazz at the Philharmonic", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["alto_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Rue Bleue", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "67254"}, {"t": "Rockin' in Rhythm", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "59436"}, {"t": "Things Ain't What They Used To Be", "c": "Mercer Ellington", "w": "11294"}, {"t": "Cotton Tail", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "30186"}, {"t": "Swamp Goo", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "67252"}, {"t": "Girdle Hurdle", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "67253"}, {"t": "Far East Suite: Mount Harissa", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "67255"}, {"t": "Tutti for Cootie", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "106809"}, {"t": "Up Jump", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "117358"}, {"t": "Second Sacred Concert: The Shepherd (Who Watches Over the Night Flock)", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "36256"}, {"t": "Very Tenor", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "67256"}]}, {"id": "19101", "date": "1967-03-26", "label": "Jazz at the Philharmonic", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["alto_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Salomé", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "117359"}, {"t": "A Chromatic Love Affair", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "117360"}, {"t": "Rue Bleue", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "67254"}, {"t": "Blood Count", "c": "Billy Strayhorn", "w": "33766"}]}, {"id": "18987", "date": "1968-04-04", "label": "Duke Ellington in His Concert of Sacred Music", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["alto_saxophone"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}], "works_created": [{"t": "Squatty Roo", "w": "5814"}], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Patricia Willard", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I was determined to hear Johnny Hodges... I said that I was studying music, and Johnny Hodges, my idol, was playing with the Duke Ellington band... And that's where I first heard Johnny Hodges and the Duke Ellington Orchestra. I didn't get a chance to say anything to any of them or anything", "doc_title": "61520_Teddy Edwards oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/61520/"}, {"speaker": "Dick Spottswood", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "The interviewee mentions Johnny Hodges in the context of music history and royalty disputes involving Duke Ellington, but does not describe a personal interaction or direct professional relationship with Hodges himself.", "doc_title": "Dick Spottswood interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, February 13, 2023", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/dick-spottswood-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-february-13-2023"}, {"speaker": "Elvin Jones", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "he had these records. Recordings of duke Ellington’s band and he used to sit there in his house and listen to Duke Ellington cause his man was Johnny Hodges so we listened to everything we had on him", "doc_title": "Elvin Jones — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Jones-Elvin/Jones_Elvin_Transcript.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Jimmy Wormworth", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "And one of his idols was Johnny Hodges at the time, curiously enough. Charlie Parker was his main idol, but he loved © Fillius Jazz Archive -15- Johnny Hodges, I think for his tone.", "doc_title": "Jimmy Wormworth interviewed by Monk Rowe, New York City, New York, January 6, 2002", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/jimmy-wormworth-interviewed-monk-rowe-new-york-city-new-york-january-6-2002"}, {"speaker": "Percy Heath", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "No, it was with Johnny Hodges and Sonny Greer. Boy, we had a good time on that gig. That was the only time I played with the Duke Ellington guys.", "doc_title": "Percy Heath — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Heath-Percy/Heath_Percy_Interview_Transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Patricia Willard", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "When I joined Duke Ellington in the Cotton Club, it was ... Johnny Hodges, and Carney, and on the drums was Sonny Greer", "doc_title": "61531_Juan Tizol oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/61531/"}]}